Women are sending a loud message to Joe Biden and Bernie Sanders this year: If either of you makes it to the White House, you must take a woman along as vice president, Dahleen Glanton writes.

That seems to be the universal and uncompromising mandate by women of all races. But some Democrats also are adding this caveat — the vice president must be an African American woman.

Choosing a black woman runninng mate would be a resounding statement that African American voters are the backbone of the Democratic Party.

30 mins ·

Coronavirus fears are causing major problems for people with obsessive-compulsive disorder and other anxiety illnesses — and psychologists are warning that it's not a joke.

“As someone recovering from OCD after a few years now, I feel as though OCD is trying to spike like there is no tomorrow,” one woman wrote on Facebook, “and I’ve been struggling to figure out what is OCD and what is just a normal response.”

News about coronavirus has taken a particularly heavy toll on the mental health of some who are already dealing with obsessive-compulsive disorder and other anxiety illnesses.
chicagotribune.com
